---
Unofficial command-line client for the Tripo 3D Generation API

Usage: tripo [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  balance             Show account balance
  upload              Upload a file, print the `file_token`
  completions         Generate shell completions
  task                Raw task escape hatches: create from JSON, get, wait, download
  text-to-model       Generate a 3D model from a text prompt
  image-to-model      Generate a 3D model from a single image
  multiview-to-model  Generate a 3D model from multi-view images
  convert-model       Convert a model to a different file format
  stylize-model       Apply a stylization preset to a model
  texture-model       (Re-)texture an existing model
  refine-model        Refine a draft model
  check-riggable      Pre-check whether a model can be rigged
  rig-model           Generate a skeletal rig for an existing model
  retarget-animation  Retarget one or more animations onto a rigged model
  mesh-segmentation   Decompose a model into semantic parts
  mesh-completion     Fill holes in an existing mesh
  smart-lowpoly       Reduce a high-poly model to a lowpoly one
  help                Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --api-key <API_KEY>
          Tripo API key. Must begin with `tsk_`

          [env: TRIPO_API_KEY]

      --region <REGION>
          API region

          Possible values:
          - global: Global endpoint (default)
          - cn:     China mainland endpoint

          [env: TRIPO_REGION=]
          [default: global]

      --base-url <BASE_URL>
          Override the API base URL (testing / staging)

      --json
          Emit structured JSON instead of human-readable tables (default if stdout is not a TTY)

      --no-color
          Disable ANSI color output

  -v, --verbose...
          Increase log verbosity (-v = debug, -vv = trace)

  -q, --quiet
          Silence info-level logs

      --force
          Overwrite existing files at output paths instead of erroring

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
